3. User Accounts vs Service Accounts (GCP)
    🔹 High‑Level Difference: User accounts are for humans interacting with GCP, while service accounts are for applications and automated processes.
    🔹 What is a Service Account? A service account is a non‑human identity used by: Applications, Virtual machines, CI/CD pipelines, Kubernetes workloads
        Example: my-service@my-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com
     Service accounts are used when: A VM accesses Cloud Storage, A Kubernetes Pod accesses Pub/Sub, A CI/CD pipeline deploys to GCP, A backend talks to another GCP service.
    ✅ Authentication (Service Account): gcloud auth activate-service-account --key-file=service-account-key.json 
        or recommended (no keys): Attached automatically to: Compute Engine, GKE, Cloud Run, App Engine.
    ✅ Why Service Accounts Are Safer: ✔ No passwords, ✔ Scoped permissions, ✔ Can be rotated, ✔ Fully auditable, ✔ Principle of least privilege.


4.  Explain gcloud configurations
    gcloud configurations let you maintain multiple named sets of CLI settings (like active account, project, region, zone) on the same machine and switch between them instantly.
      In simple terms: configurations = profiles for the gcloud CLI.
    ✅ Why configurations are needed
        Without configurations, you’d constantly: 
            Switch projects manually
            Switch accounts manually
            Risk running commands in the wrong environment (e.g., prod)
        With configurations, you can safely separate:
            dev / qa / prod
            personal / work accounts
            different client projects

    ✅ What does a configuration store?
        Each configuration can store values like:
            Account (user or service account)
            Project
            Region
            Zone
            Other CLI preferences
        Each configuration is isolated from the others.
    ✅ Default configuration (always exists)
        When you install gcloud, it creates: default
        to check it run:        gcloud config configurations list
    ✅ Common configuration commands 
        🔹 Create a new configuration:                    gcloud config configurations create dev
        🔹 Activate (switch to) a configuration:          gcloud config configurations activate dev
        🔹 Set values in a configuration:                 gcloud config set project my-dev-project
                                                          gcloud config set account dev-user@company.com
                                                          gcloud config set compute/region asia-south1
                                                          gcloud config set compute/zone asia-south1-a
        These settings apply only to the active configuration
        🔹 Delete a configuration:                        gcloud config configurations delete dev
        
            
